reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Easy to install, very nice!
reviews.reviewText: Order arrived as specified. The pans felt of good quality and not cheaply made, it was easy to install and the heat coils fit right in without any problems. For my GE range, these pans are 'Type B' as specified by the range manufacturer. I did pose a question on what type these were (A or B), but received no answers, so since I was anxious to replace the cheap ones I had, I just went ahead and ordered them. Thankfully, I wasn't disappointed, am very happy with the product. Definitely will order again when needed.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 14, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The media could not be loaded. Replaced my old ones with these, it has been a couple months and they have held up decently well. They fit perfectly in my GE electric stove. I have washed and scrubbed them, put them in the dishwasher, and they have held up well. The paint has worn away a bit on the burner that I use the most. It does look a bit rusty/ worn. By the time I move out, they will definitely need to be replaced. But it’s worth the money if you want something that hold up and will probably lasts longer than other types of aluminum or foil kinds.In the video and pictures, they are clean. They were just scrubbed and washed earlier in the day. So that is how they look after a couple months of use. It all depends how frequently you cook and clean them as well. I cook every day and clean them weekly so they have definitely worn down a bit

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Fit perfectly & look great
reviews.reviewText: Replaced all four burner pans on my Hotpoint

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 4, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Woulda gave five stars but one pan was too big.
reviews.reviewText: I was actually surprised these fit for my GE electric stove top; I have gotten a few different types from stores around my area with no avail. Always had an issue with putting the burner back on over the drip pan. These fit the burner perfectly! One of the larger drip pans was a bit small so I had to push aggressively to get it flat. It is still a little tilted so I put it in the back were it’s not used all the time, just every now and again. Overall all, happy with the product; all but one drip pan was perfect and makes my stove look 100% better! Now to get some new burners. The finish is as described and with a black stove, the black pan works well!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 4, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars These are great as they look sharp when installed, they clean easily.
reviews.reviewText: I love the way these look installed on the stove! These last better than the silver and they don't chip. They are easy to clean.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 30, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars No More Rusty Drip Pans!!
reviews.reviewText: The plain metal drip pans always got rusty, black patches on them (especially when my son and husband didn't watch boiling pots). These, so far, clean up and look like new after such 'accidents'. My only concern is that the large ones are a VERY tight fit - don't know if it's because of the enamel coating? The small ones go right in; the large ones I have to 'pop' them in and then they're hard to get out to clean (thankfully it's not as often as with the silver ones). Overall, though, I really love these enameled ones!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 2, 2024
reviews.reviewText: These sat slightly deeper than original ones which helped align the burner with the socket the burner plugs into. I paired these up with the s union brand burners an they fit tight and sat evenly no burner movement. Very happy and recommend highly. Sure helped my old 40yr old hotpoint stove perform like new. Hope this review helps others
